 A FLIGHT from Germany to America was forced to make an emergency landing at Glasgow Airport earlier today. 
 The flight from Frankfurt to Dallas declared an emergency and landed in Glasgow at around 12.15pm, with emergency services meeting the plane on the runway. 
It is understood that the issue was with one of the engines on the American Airlines flight.
A spokesman for Glasgow Airport said: &quot;An American Airlines flight diverted to Glasgow Airport at around 12.15pm.
“It was met on the runway by emergency services as a precaution. The emergency has now been stood down.
“Airport services were not affected by the incident.”

